    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Species of pine native to the southeastern area of North America, having a variable form and reaching 30 m in height. It produces soft, pale yellow, easily worked wood primarily used for millwork, interior trim, toys, and siding.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
